<P>Be&s;ides impiety, di&s;content carries along
with it, as its in&s;eparable concomitants,
&s;everal other &s;inful pa&s;&s;ions. It implies
pride; or an unrea&s;onable e&s;timation of
our own merit, in compari&s;on with others.
<PB N="159" REF="170">
It implies covetou&s;ne&s;s, or an inordinate
