as the only real goods. It implies,
and always engenders, envy, or ill nature,
and hatred towards all whom we &s;ee ri&s;ing
above us in the world. Dare we treat that
as a &s;light infirmity, or a con&s;titutional
weakne&s;s merely, which imports &s;ome of
the wor&s;t di&s;po&s;itions and pa&s;&s;ions of the
human heart?&mdash;The di&s;contented man
