him. He is equally above envying the
<PB N="166" REF="177">
greate&s;t, or de&s;pi&s;ing the meane&s;t, of his
&s;ubjects.&mdash;His di&s;pen&s;ations, it is true, are
often dark and unaccountable to us; but
