vain. Every event has its own determined
<PB N="415" REF="426">
direction. That chaos of human affairs
and intrigues, where we can &s;ee no light;
that ma&s;s of di&s;order and confu&s;ion which
they often pre&s;ent to our view, is all clear|ne&s;s
and order in the &s;ight of Him who is
